com.infosense.ibilling.server.ws
Interface WSSecured

All Known Implementing Classes:
AgeingWS, BillingProcessWS, InvoiceWS, MediationConfigurationWS, OrderWS, PartnerWS, PaymentWS, PluggableTaskWS, UserTransitionResponseWS, UserWS
public interface WSSecured

Interface that marks a Web Service object as being "secure" within an entity. WSSecured objects may only be accessed and modified by web service users (callers) within the same entity as the object being accessed/modified. Implementing classes must be able to provide either an entity id or user id for the owner of the object.

Method Summary
 java.lang.Integer getOwningEntityId()
          Returns the entity ID of the company owning the secure object, or null if the entity ID is not available.
 java.lang.Integer getOwningUserId()
          Returns the user ID of the user owning the secure object, or null if the user ID is not available.
